fips: Federal Information Processing Standard (FIPS) county code
houses_tot: Number of housing units per capita
edu_low: Proportion with less than high school education
edu_mid: Proportion with high school degree or some college
edu_high: Proportion with bachelor's degree or higher
edu_low_age_18: Proportion aged 18-44 with less than high school education
edu_low_age_45: Proportion aged 45-64 with less than high school education
edu_low_age_65: Proportion aged 65+ with less than high school education
edu_mid_age_18: Proportion aged 18-44 with high school degree or some college
edu_mid_age_45: Proportion aged 45-64 with high school degree or some college
edu_mid_age_65: Proportion aged 65+ with high school degree or some college
edu_high_age_18: Proportion aged 18-44 with bachelor's degree or higher
edu_high_age_45: Proportion aged 45-64 with bachelor's degree or higher
edu_high_age_65: Proportion aged 65+ with bachelor's degree or higher
dem: Proportion of Dem votes out of dem and repub votes
repub: Proportion of Repub votes out of dem and repub votes
target: Binary indicator (1 if Democratic winner, 0 if Republican winner)
